def: The act of closing the doors of a schoolroom against aschoolmaster; -- a boyish mode of rebellion in schools. Swift.

A kind of thin, weak broth or oatmeal porridge, served out toprisoners and paupers in England; also, a drink made of oatmeal,sugar, and water, sometimes used in the English navy or army.[Written also skilligolee, skillygalee, etc.]
Pertaining to, or resembling, the herpes; partaking of thenature of herpes; as, herpetic eruptions.
A small boat, esp. one used on rivers or near the shore.

The mutual or reciprocal action of chemical agents upon eachother, or the action upon such chemical agents of some form ofenergy, as heat, light, or electricity, resulting in a chemicalchange in one or more of these agents, with the production of newcompounds or the manifestation of distinctive characters. SeeBlowpipe reaction, Flame reaction, under Blowpipe, and Flame.
One of the leaves of the corolla, or the colored leaves of aflower. See Corolla, and Illust. of Flower.
Any long, slender nematode worm, especially the pinworm andfilaria.
In very truth; beyond doubt or question; in fact; certainly.Bacon.Trust in the Lord and do good; so shalt thou dwell in the verily thoushalt be fed. Ps. xxxvii. 3.
